# Project Setup Guide

This project can be started either locally or with Docker. The steps below are intended for anyone cloning the repository from GitHub for the first time.

## Prerequisites

Make sure you have installed:
- Git
- Node.js 20+
- npm
- Docker and Docker Compose

## 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <your-github-repo-url>
cd dockerfile
```

## 2. Start the backend

From the project root:

```bash
npm install
npm start
```

The backend will run on:
- http://localhost:4000

You can also use:

```bash
npm run start-dev
```

## 3. Start the frontend

Open a second terminal and run:

```bash
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev
```

The frontend will run on:
- http://localhost:5173

## 4. Start everything with Docker (recommended)

From the project root:

```bash
docker compose up --build
```

This will start:
- Backend API on http://localhost:4000
- Frontend on http://localhost:5173
- MongoDB container
- Mongo Express on http://localhost:8081
- Redis container

To stop the containers:

```bash
docker compose down
```

## 5. Optional environment file

If you want to customize settings, create a `.env` file in the project root before running Docker.

Example:

```env
PORT=4000
```

## 6. Useful commands

```bash
# Backend
npm start
npm run start-dev

# Frontend
cd frontend
npm install
npm run dev

# Docker
docker compose up --build
docker compose down
```

If you encounter issues, make sure Docker is running and that no other service is already using ports 4000, 5173, 8081, or 27017.